name: Ol' Crow Crew No. 2: Black Vincent and The Duc of Orange
description:
Deep in the wide Sargasso Drift, Captain Panik and the Ol' Crow Crew live on love, plunder and warpsauce. Hard liquor and fist fighting forever!
Black Vincent’s ride, The Duc of Orange, is by far the sleekest vehicle in the Crew: a quad turbofan unlimited atmosphere bike built by the elder of the greatest racing clan of Celeritas 3. Vince insists he won the Duc in fair and open competition, but an explanation more generally believed is that it was acquired after a disagreement between Vince and the elder: he believed Vince  wouldn’t just murder him for the vehicle,  Vince disagreed.
In battle, Black Vincent and The Duc of Orange are first to the fight, bringing the pain along with the vanguard of other speedy crewsters, like Scratchnasty and Vince’s biker rival, Fat Bob on The Octopus.
Between raids, Vince can be found home in the warping scablands, bullseyeing squigrats, even though they’re not much bigger than two metres.
Scratchbuilt model, photographed and altered digitally, one of a series with interlocking narratives.
